By Emmanuel Okogba Super Falcons forward, Asisat Oshoala will play no further part in the side’s campaign at the ongoing Women’s Africa Cup of Nations, WAFCON, owing to an injury. The disclosure was made on the official Twitter handle of the Nigeria Football Federation, NFF, on Wednesday afternoon. Oshoala was involved in a tackle with a South African defender when they met on Monday but shrugged it off and continued to play before she was replaced by Francisca Ordega in the 81st minute. The tweet read: “Sad news from @NGSuper_Falcons camp: Top striker @AsisatOshoala is out of the ongoing #WAFCON2022. She sustained a Grade 2 Medial Collateral Ligament strain in the game against South Africa. She is due back in Spain on Thursday. Get well quick Asisat! Oshoala’s just concluded club football season was plagued with injuries that led to her having a lengthy spell on the sideline at Barcelona. She also missed the WAFCON qualifier against Ivory Coast in February.   Head Coach Randy Waldrum has invited 32 players to the camp of the Super Falcons as the Cup holders get set for a two-week training camp in Morocco ahead of the 12th Women Africa Cup of Nations holding in that country, 2nd – 23rd July. Goalkeeper Chiamaka Nnadozie, defender and… In "Sports" By Emmanuel Okogba Asisat Oshoala, Super Falcons striker and four times African Women's Player of the Year has signed a contract extension with Barcelona Femeni that will see her remain at the club until 2024. The announcement was made on the official Twitter handle of the club that had a… In "Sports" Asisat Oshoala, a Nigeria International baller has had a successful career from the beginning. In "News"